Jen Miller https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jen_Miller 0 Jennifer "Jen" Miller (also known as Saint Reverend Jen and Reverend Jen — born Jennifer Miller on July 24, 1972 in Silver Spring, Maryland) is an American performer, actress, writer, painter, director, preacher, and poet from Manhattan, New York City. In 2002 Miller was named the Village Voice's "Best D.I.Y. Go-Girl" in the category of "Over 21".
